OL,3,CMountains of rubbish after tidal wave
OL,4,Cof plastic covers Bali beach
OL,6,FLocals are confident, however, that
OL,7,Fvisitors will return once the rubbish
OL,8,Fis removed.
OL,10,FPaulina Kaka, who lives in the
OL,11,FKedonganan area, said: "If the trash
OL,12,Fis cleaned, this place will be more
OL,13,Fbeautiful to see, and more people will
OL,14,Fcome here."
OL,16,FA local environment agency official
OL,17,Fsaid the wave of rubbish on Kedonganan
OL,18,Fbeach is something that happens
OL,19,Fannually due to the monsoon weather.
